# Error handling and observability

- Use Nest HTTP exceptions (`UnauthorizedException`, `NotFoundException`, etc.) for API errors.
- Map infrastructure failures (e.g. federated MySQL unavailable) to `503` with a safe message — no stack traces to clients.
- Log with `Logger`: include operation and ids where useful; never log secrets or full tokens.
- Re-throw unknown errors after logging; do not swallow exceptions with empty `catch`.
